nginx is what I was assigned
open ports needed, 80 for http, 443 for https and 22 for ssh purposes are as follows, for 80 normal web traffic, for 443, secure traffic, for 22 for server managing
outbound ports is 80 443 and 53, with 80 and 443 being for internet and 53 for dns, with the purposes being 80 for package updates, 443 for ssl certificates, and 53 for domain name
for security group, 80 and 443 are anywhere and 22 is admin ip, this would be inbound
outbound, allow all
firewall, use ufw, for example 
sudo ufw allow 80
sudo ufw allow 443
sudo ufw allow from ADMIN_IP to any port 22

configuration
main configurations for ngnix 
/etc/nginx/nginx.conf
/etc/nginx/sites-available/
/etc/nginx/sites-enabled/

create 2 site config files

/etc/nginx/sites-available/site1.conf
/etc/nginx/sites-available/site2.conf

enabling them
/etc/nginx/sites-enabled/
each site gets its own block
virtual hosts
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name site1.example.com;

    root /var/www/site1;
    index index.html;

    location / {
        try_files $uri $uri/ =404;
    }
}

server {
    listen 80;
    server_name site2.example.com;

    root /var/www/site2;
    index index.html;

    location / {
        try_files $uri $uri/ =404;
    }
}

dns / host configuration
site1.example.com → SERVER_IP
site2.example.com → SERVER_IP
modify within /etc/hosts

